Interface BypassableCommand<InputType>

All Known Implementing Classes:
Chain, CommandBase, DelegatorCommand, EvaluateRouter, ExceptionHandlerInterpolation, FilterChain, ForLoop, InterpolationCommand, OgnlRouter, OperationSpecificClientProcessorsInterpolation, OperationSpecificProcessorsInterpolation, ParallelChain, PostProcessorsInterpolation, PreProcessorsInterpolation, ProxyTypeRouter, Router, ServiceSpecificClientProcessorsInterpolation, ServiceSpecificProcessorsInterpolation, SetCommand, SplitterAggregator, TenantRouter
public interface BypassableCommand<InputType>
Implement this interface if a command can be bypassed. By doing so, we can economize on resources dedicated to this command if it needs to be bypassed. Some implementations use this feature (see ParallelChain for example)
Author:
Raja Shankar Kolluru
